description.p:
cleaning a surface of a single crystal substrate;


contacting said cleaned surface with a polar organic compound so that said cleaned surface adsorbs said polar compound;


applying a hydrocarbon solvent solution containing at least one organic group-containing metal compound on said polar organic compound-adsorbed surface; and


then heating said substrate to decompose said organic group-containing metal compound and to form a dense epitaxial metal oxide film on said substrate.
